issue.body:
This is a crazy one, but after upgrading from 10.0.0 to 10.1.0 a bunch of my ProjectTo calls starting throwing "Operation could destabilize the runtime" from within NHibernate. I've spent some time narrowing it down to a simple(ish) repro:


### Source/destination types

```csharp
public class NormalizationSegment
{
    public virtual long Id { get; set; }
    // When this is decimal I get the error, when it's decimal? it works
    public virtual decimal StartCharge { get; set; }
}

public class NormalizationSegmentModel
{
    public long Id { get; set; }
    public decimal? StartCharge { get; set; }
}
```

### Mapping configuration

```csharp
var config = new MapperConfiguration(cfg =>
{
    cfg.CreateMap<NormalizationSegment, NormalizationSegmentModel>();
});

config.AssertConfigurationIsValid();
```

### AutoMapper Version: 10.1.0, NHibernate 5.3.3, FluentNHibernate 3.0.1, .NET Framework 4.8

### Expected behavior

No exception

### Actual behavior

A VerificationException is thrown with the text "Operation could destabilize the runtime." from the depths of NHibernate.

### Steps to reproduce

When the code executes, and there is data returned by the query, the exception is thrown during the materialization of the results. Changing the source type of the problematic property to be decimal? to match the destination type does not throw the exception.

```csharp
var mapper = config.CreateMapper();

using (var sessionFactory = CreateSessionFactory())
using (var session = sessionFactory.OpenSession())
using (var tx = session.BeginTransaction())
{
    var segments = session.Query<NormalizationSegment>();

    // This call throws VerificationError "Operation could destabilize the runtime"
    // (so long as rows are returned from the database)
    var results = mapper.ProjectTo<NormalizationSegmentModel>(segments)
        .ToList();

    tx.Commit();
}
```

### Additional configuration needed

```csharp
public static ISessionFactory CreateSessionFactory()
{
    return Fluently.Configure()
        .Database(MsSqlConfiguration.MsSql2012
            .ConnectionString(c => c.FromConnectionStringWithKey("TestDB")))
        .Mappings(m =>
            m.FluentMappings
                .AddFromAssemblyOf<Program>()
                .Conventions.AddFromAssemblyOf<Program>())
        .BuildSessionFactory();
}

public class NormalizationSegmentMap : ClassMap<NormalizationSegment>
{
    public NormalizationSegmentMap()
    {
        Id(x => x.Id);
        Map(x => x.StartCharge);
    }
}
```
